===Etymology===
The copula {{m|ja|です|tr=desu}} is thought to be a contracted version of {{m|ja|である|であります|tr=dearimasu}}, from {{compound|だ|alt1=で|tr1=de|ある|alt2=あります|tr2=arimasu|lang=ja|nocat=1}}; however, there are other possibilities, namely {{m|ja|でござる|でございます|tr=degozaimasu}}, from {{compound|だ|alt1=で|tr1=de|ござる|alt2=ございます|tr2=gozaimasu|lang=ja|nocat=1}}; {{m|ja|でする|tr=desuru}}, from {{compound|だ|alt1=で|tr1=de|する|tr2=suru|lang=ja|nocat=1}}; {{m|ja|でおわす|tr=deowasu}}, from {{compound|だ|alt1=で|tr1=de|おわす|tr2=owasu|lang=ja|nocat=1}}; and {{m|ja|でそうろう|tr=desourou}}, from {{compound|だ|alt1=で|tr1=de|そうろう|tr2=sourou|lang=ja|nocat=1}}.

===Verb===
{{ja-verb}}

# To [[be]].
# {{non-gloss definition|Used to express politeness toward the listener.}}

====Usage notes====
Perfective form is {{m|ja|でした|tr=deshita}}, volitional {{m|ja|でしょう|tr=deshou}}, conjunctive {{m|ja|でして|tr=deshite}}. Other forms are not used.

Replaces {{m|ja|だ|tr=da}} in cases of nouns and adjectives which it is used with, e.g. {{lang|ja|[[犬]]だ}} becomes {{lang|ja|犬です}} and {{lang|ja|[[綺麗]]だ}} becomes {{lang|ja|綺麗です}}. Similarly, {{m|ja|でしょう|tr=deshou}} replaces {{m|ja|だろう|tr=darou}} and {{m|ja|でして|tr=deshite}} replaces {{m|ja|で|tr=de}}.

{{m|ja|です|tr=desu}} attaches as is to adjectives used without {{l|ja|だ|tr=da}}, e.g. {{lang|ja|[[美しい]]}} becomes {{lang|ja|美しいです}} and {{lang|ja|美しかった}} becomes {{lang|ja|美しかったです}}. Forms such as {{lang|ja|美しいでした}} and {{lang|ja|美しいでして}} are nonstandard. For the forms {{m|ja|ない|ないです|tr=nai desu}} and {{m|ja|ない|なかったです|tr=nakatta desu}}, there are synonyms {{m|ja|ありません|tr=arimasen}} and {{m|ja|ありません|ありませんでした|tr=arimasen deshita}}.

